reviews.review_text: outstanding Thanks for the upgrade!! I am not terribly familiar with the existing one in circulation but I can say with full confidence that this one is SMOKIN, very clear especially considering that it was recorded 42 years ago. I am kinda partial to the previous night but this is a real treat. Thanks again for taking the time to polish this gem!! This is certainly worth taking for a spin.

The GRATEFUL DEAD "Live On Stage" July 30, 1966 at the P.N.E. Auditorium, B.C. Canada ~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~

5 stars for the mix
5 stars for the recording
5 stars for the performance

In the pocket, solid show from Vancouver. 

A "MUST HAVE" for any collector of 1966 GRATEFUL DEAD.

Get both shows, July 29 & 30, 1966.

Eat, Drink, Be Merry and Listen to the GRATEFUL DEAD.

Thanks for the Love from V.BC. 1966.

The Grateful Dead: Show #46? 47???  (pt. 2) Good evening Captain Consciousness! **Single applause**... "Our fame has preceded us". More classic Dead humor.

Great show... Really made a push further than the night before. Great sound quality. Phil bomb! What can I say, Cream Puff War blew me away... What a set closer. This is the reason the Dead got popular. Not the "best" version of Viola Lee I've heard, but it had an unmistakable quality to it that made it amazing. I just love Phil's intro. Where's the Dick's Pick's for this show?.. Have to wait to see in Dave's Picks. BIODTL and GMLSG, definitely above average (which is saying a lot). Trips Festival... What a trip.

Work all night sure gettin' stoned tonight Amazing show. The lack of applause proves they were simply way ahead of their time.
This is so good, somebody should break into archive's server room just to steal the flacs. VBR mp3 isn't enough!

one gem the only gem of this horrible show is Cream Puff War.
the rest sound like they are at practice. 
Pigpens quivering , flat singing is unbearable, just a horrible singer.
As Kev puts it "way ahead of their time" is a joke, high school garage bands sound better than these guys here.
Futuristic Music one of my best GD songs and tempo Best of the best forward looking for acoustic perfection in the whole body of GD works.
